# GSAP ScrollTrigger Patterns

## Pinned Sections with Scroll-Driven Content

When creating scroll-locked sections that change content based on scroll progress:

```typescript
// Use refs to track state without triggering ScrollTrigger recreation
const activeIndexRef = useRef(0);
const [activeIndex, setActiveIndex] = useState(0);

useLayoutEffect(() => {
  const st = ScrollTrigger.create({
    trigger: container,
    start: 'top top+=160', // Account for fixed header
    end: `+=${totalScrollDistance}`,
    pin: true,
    pinSpacing: true,
    onUpdate: (self) => {
      const newIndex = Math.floor(self.progress * totalItems);
      // Compare with ref, not state, to avoid dependency issues
      if (newIndex !== activeIndexRef.current) {
        activeIndexRef.current = newIndex;
        setActiveIndex(newIndex);
      }
    },
  });
  return () => st.kill();
}, [modalities.length]); // Only depend on array length, NOT activeIndex
```

## Scroll Distance Calculation

- Use `window.innerHeight * 0.4` per item for light, natural feel
- Higher values (0.6-0.8) create "sticky" feeling that requires more effort

## Direction-Aware Parallax Transitions

```typescript
// Track previous index to determine scroll direction
const prevIndexRef = useRef(0);
const isScrollingDown = activeIndex > prevIndexRef.current;
const yStart = isScrollingDown ? 30 : -30;

gsap.fromTo(elements, 
  { opacity: 0, y: yStart },
  { opacity: 1, y: 0, duration: 0.5, stagger: 0.04, ease: 'power3.out' }
);
```

## Excluding Pinned Sections from Page Fade Transitions

When page has fade transitions between sections, exclude pinned sections:

```typescript
sections.forEach((section, index) => {
  const sectionId = section.id;
  
  // Skip pinned sections - they handle their own visibility
  if (sectionId === 'pinned-section-id') {
    gsap.set(section, { opacity: 1 });
    return;
  }
  // ... fade logic for other sections
});
```
